description:
Convert these traditional functions to arrow functions:

1. function square(x) { return x * x; }
2. function isEven(num) { return num % 2 === 0; }
3. function getFullName(first, last) { return first + ' ' + last; }

Use the shortest form possible!

instructions:
Convert these traditional functions to arrow functions:

1. function square(x) { return x * x; }
2. function isEven(num) { return num % 2 === 0; }
3. function getFullName(first, last) { return first + ' ' + last; }

Use the shortest form possible!

commonMistakes.correction:
Forgetting curly braces for multi-line:
   const greet = name =>
     let msg = 'Hello';
     return msg;  // WRONG - syntax error

   const greet = name => {
     let msg = 'Hello';
     return msg;  // CORRECT
   };
